KWAZULU-NATAL - The KwaZulu-Natal High Court ruled on Friday that the Nazereth Baptist Church (Shembe) members should vote for a new church leader. The church has been embroiled in a leadership dispute since 2011. [BREAKING] Shembe church members to go on ballot to decide the church leader #ShembeAppeal Mduduzi Shembe, the son of the church founder, and his uncle Vela Shembe were locked in a bruising legal battle over who would succeed founder Vimbeni Shembe. He filed an appeal after losing the leadership battle to his uncle in May 2016. eNCA